    • deleteSubtree

      public RTree<D,T>.Node deleteSubtree(D[][] dimensions)
      Similar to delete(Comparable[][]), but this will remove an entire subtree and return it to the caller. Where as delete(Comparable[][]) promotes all child nodes of a deleted node to the parent node, this simply removes the entire tree and returns it. This is O(n) where n is the size of the subtree. This is required to accurately adjust the collection size.
      Parameters:
      dimensions - The dimensions of a node to remove along with all it's children.
      Returns:
      The removed node.

    • isInside

      protected int isInside(D[][] d1, D[][] d2)
      Return if d1 is INSIDE, OUTSIDE, or at the SAME level in the tree relative to d2. Each pari of upper and lower values are compared using isInside(Comparable[], Comparable[]) to do the comparison.
      Parameters:
      d1 - An array of 2-dimensions value pairs where d1[i][0] is the lower bound and d1[i][1] is the upper bound.
      d2 - An array of 2-dimensions value pairs where d2[i][0] is the lower bound and d2[i][1] is the upper bound.
      Returns:
      if d1 is INSIDE, OUTSIDE, or at the SAME level in the tree relative to d2.
      See Also:
      • isInside(Comparable[], Comparable[])

    • isInside

      protected int isInside(D[] d1, D[] d2)
      Return if d1 is INSIDE, OUTSIDE, or at the SAME level in the tree relative to d2. This implementation considers that equal values are eligible to be inside. There is an intentional bias to have d1 be placed INSIDE d2 if the dimensions are all equal. This implementation may be overwritten if the user desires different comparison behavior.
      Parameters:
      d1 - A two-dimensional array where index 0 is the lower bound and index 1 is the upper bound.
      d2 - A two-dimensional array where index 0 is the lower bound and index 1 is the upper bound.
      Returns:
      if d1 is INSIDE, OUTSIDE, or at the SAME level in the tree relative to d2.
